node.bodyText:
@MartimSalgado  Couple of things:

I have to comment out some blocks that use your own staff.
Since you use VI solver, you should set use_snes_vi_solver = true
You used 8 levels of refinement which seems to be too many. I suggest starting with a uniform mesh to identify the convergence issue.
You have two identical BC blocks, top_x and bottom_x
@hugary1995 and I found an error of jacobian calculation in ComputeLinearElasticPFFractureStress::computeStrainSpectral It should not affect the convergence much because of using PJFNK, but we still need to fix it as soon as we can.
